mdElement.text: Created by application server upon startup.
Resource adapter bootstrap process may include submitting work requests to application server.
Work instance for the bootstrapping process.
Resource adapter submits further work requests in context of normal resource adapter usage.
<<responsibility>> - To create instances of managed connections. - To create instances of virtual client connection factories.

<<responsibility>> - Bootstraps and shuts down adapter. - Activates/deactivates msg end points. - Provides application server a mechanism to regain after crash a handle to the XA resourcces for that adapter to clean up pending transactions.
<<responsibility>> The physical connection to the EIS contained within a connection pool anaged by the application server.
<<responsibility>> Provide clients virtual connections which provide a client interface to the EIS.

<<responsibility>> A virtual client connection which provides the client interface to the EIS. The application server manages the coupling between the virtual client connections and the physical managed connections.
Used by resource manager (e.g. application server).
